cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a method to scale MAP-Elites to high-dimensional controllers parameterized by large neural networks. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method for post-damage recovery in a difficult high-dimensional control task. 

The paper also falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics) as it discusses the application of QD algorithms in enabling real robots to recover quickly from joint damage and evolving robot morphologies to discover new gaits. 

The sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a method to efficiently explore high-dimensional control tasks with strongly deceptive rewards. 

The paper also falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a new hybrid algorithm for post-damage recovery in a difficult high-dimensional control task. 

Finally, the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper discusses the application of QD algorithms in enabling real robots to recover quickly from joint damage and evolving robot morphologies to discover new gaits, which are relevant to systems and control.
